import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temperature'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of temperature throughout the year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.scatter(data['pressure'], data['wind'])
    plt.xlabel('Pressure')
    plt.ylabel('Wind')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the relationship between pressure and wind?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='temperature', by='day_night')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature during the day and night?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Day/Night')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
